Patch summary:
Keep target-files signing from crashing on embedded OTA zips that do not need
boot OTA regeneration, and preserve a signed 16K boot image when present.

Recent releasetools detects embedded payload OTA zips inside target_files and
passes them through SignOtaPackage. For Cuttlefish page-size boot OTAs,
RegenerateBootOTA can intentionally decide that no regenerated OTA is needed
(for example the non-incremental 16K boot OTA), but it used to leave the temp
OTA file empty. SignOtaPackage then opened that empty file as a zip and aborted
with zipfile.BadZipFile.

When regeneration is skipped, copy the original embedded OTA into the temp file
so the normal payload-signing path still has a valid OTA zip to process.

Also re-sign IMAGES/boot_16k.img and write it into the signed target-files zip.
The normal boot image is regenerated during signing, but the 16K alternate boot
image can otherwise be skipped because it is not named IMAGES/boot.img.

